---

I. The Sideline Perspective

> ‚ÄúAngels on the sideline, puzzled and amused‚Ä¶‚Äù

The metaphor of observers‚Äîperhaps higher intelligences or simply one's own elevated cognition‚Äîcasts light on the absurdity of human self-destruction when viewed from a place of detached clarity. The angels‚Äô bewilderment is not malicious, but tragicomic. It is the gaze of one who sees what could be, and what is, and mourns the gap between them.

