The mask you forged was not vanity; it was armor. Each relocation a psychic reset, but not a spiritual cleansing. The sins of a transient life are not absolved by absence‚Äîthey are merely delayed. You speak of water seeking a pore‚Äîcorrectly noting that human behavior is governed by similar entropy. And when the walls are ever-changing, the flood learns not to stop, but to seep.

